Title : Jerzy Langer
Text : '''Jerzy Marian Langer''' (born 18 July 1947, Łódź, Poland) is a [[Polish people|Polish]] [[physicist]] specializing in [[condensed matter physics]]. He is a professor at the Institute of Physics of the [[Polish Academy of Sciences]].<ref name="cv">[http://www.ae-info.org/ae/User/Langer_Jerzy/CV Curriculum vitae], [[Academia Europaea]], retrieved 2014-05-05.</ref>

==Awards and honors==
Langer became a [[fellow]] of the [[American Physical Society]] in 1989 "for contributions in the area of defects and recombination phenomena in semiconductors and ionic solids."<ref>[http://www.aps.org/programs/honors/fellowships/archive-all.cfm?initial=L&year=2013&unit_id=&institution= APS Fellow Archive], accessed 2014-05-06.</ref> He is also a fellow of the [[Warsaw Scientific Society]],<ref>[http://www.tnw.waw.pl/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=71&Itemid=34 Member list], Warsaw Scientific Society (in Polish), retrieved 2014-05-06.</ref> and [[Academia Europaea]].<ref name="cv"/>

